cd to the directory where you have your "Dockerfile"

To Build Dcoker Image:
   docker build -t springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE . 

To check docker images:
    docker images  

To run a docker image:
     docker run -p 8080:8080 springboot-docker-demo 
                   or
     docker run -p 8081:8080 springboot-docker-demo 
     Note: Here 8081 is the host port and 8080 is the container port

To check the docker containers running:
    docker ps 

To start a docker container in a detached mode:
     docker run -p 8081:8080 -d springboot-docker-demo

To see the logs on the docker container running in detached mode:
     docker logs -f 7d5f    (Note: Here 7d5f are the first four characters of the docker container running)

To stop the docker container running in detached mode:
     docker stop 7d5f 

Docker login:
     docker login  

To link a docker image with a repository on docker hub:
      docker tag springboot-docker-demo mehdavi/springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE
      docker push mehdavi/springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE 
      docker pull mehdavi/springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE   
      docker run -p 8080:8080 mehdavi/springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE 

To create a docker network to bridge containers in docker:
     docker network create springboot-mysql-net

To check the list of all docker networks:
     docker network ls

To run a docker image in a docker container in a network:
     docker run --network springboot-mysql-net --name sqldb -e "ACCEPT_EULA=1" -e "MSSQL_SA_PASSWORD=MyStrongPass123" -e "MSSQL_PID=Developer" -e "MSSQL_USER=SA" -e "MYSQL_DATABASE"=employeedb -p 1434:1434 -d mcr.microsoft.com/azure-sql-edge
To run another docker image in a container in the same network:
     docker run --network springboot-mysql-net --name springboot-mysql-container -p 8088:8088 -d springboot-restful-webservices 
     (docker run --network <Network Name> --name <Container Name> -p 8088:8088 -d <Image Name>)
To check the logs if container is running in detached (-d) mode:
     docker logs -f f80d 

To access mysql in the docker container:
     docker exec -it sqldb bash
     mysql -u root -p

To forcefully remove a docker image:
     docker rmi -f <provide docker container id here>


Docker Compose Commonds(Provided that you are in the project directory):
   To pull the image from the docker hub and star it in a docker container:
      docker-compose up
   To pull the image from the docker hub and start it in a docker container detached:
      docker-compose -d
      docker-compose up --build  (Note: To bring up two containers. Spring boot needs to be prepared locally)
   To check the logs:
      docker logs -f <docker container name>
   To stop all docker containers running in the background:
     docker-compose down
